<p>Welcome to the BYU-Idaho English Department's student webpage. Within these pages, you will find resources for your <a href="http://www.byui.edu/english/students/apa-resources">papers</a>, projects, <a href="http://www.byui.edu/english/students/english-majors-and-minors">schooling</a>, and most importantly that craving for more <a href="http://www.byui.edu/english/students/scholastic">books.</a></p>
<p>One of the great apects of being associated with the English department is the many opportunities students have for <a href="http://www.byui.edu/english/students/internships">internships</a>, retreats, and <a href="http://www.byui.edu/english/students/calls-for-papers">conference presentations.</a></p>
<p>If you have questions about becoming an English major or minor, browse through the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/english/students/prospective-student">prospective student</a> page or visit the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/english/students/english-advising">Advising center.</a></p>
